    "updated_at": "2015-05-29T08:07:48Z",
    "body": "If revocation's the only goal you can also designate other people's keys as revokers. I.e. you don't need any of a key's secret material to revoke it.\n\nLook at the [GPG documentation](https://gnupg.org/documentation/manuals/gnupg/OpenPGP-Key-Management.html#OpenPGP-Key-Management) for the `addrevoker` command (in the `--edit-key` menu) and the `--desig-revoke` command line option to gpg.\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
